text:
🇵🇪 maría elena moyano 🇵🇪 "a woman of african descent, she came from the “pueblos jóvenes,” or shanty towns, on the wastelands of the capital’s outskirts where hundreds of thousands (millions today) of peruvians found a space in which to build a future. and with the community organizations that she and others helped create and lead, they helped transform these squatter wastelands into new cities.

it was in these pueblos jóvenes that people from all over the country and from all cultural traditions came together to build schools, houses and public places. maría elena’s awareness of how women were excluded even in the poorest settings drove her to community work. at 25, she was elected sub-secretary general of the newly-created federación popular de mujeres de villa el salvador, and two years later was elected its president.

seven years later, the violence of peru’s internal struggle caught up with her. seizing and eliminating the independent leadership of the popular neighborhoods around lima, and specifically of the emblematic villa el salvador, was part of the strategy of the sendero luminoso. on february 15, 1992, sendero luminoso forces marched into the town, killed her, and then dynamited her lifeless body—perhaps as an example and a threat, or even as an expression of racism. [credit:americas quarterly, carolina trivelli]
-
-
-
-

text:
this is the symbol for survivor 
i relate to this in ways 
that on some days 
i dont even want to face the day 
or get out of bed
because of the sights 
you put in my head 
because of you 
i was terrified 
to go outside 
and see the sunrise 
but for some reason i never said no 
which doesn't mean yes
but for you it seemed apparent 
that my unsaid answer was a go ahead 
well it wasn't you fool 
but it wasn't okay 
not any of the days
but from that i learned
so many things 
i learned to say no 
and go away 
and from overcoming
the terrible circumstances 
i am alive today
and i'm not afraid 
#metoo #sad  #sadpoems  #metoo #metoomovement #writing #poetry  #freeversepoetry  #truth

text: 1st time i dated a 🇺🇸 person/woman- 1987 😳😂on my virgin (& extended) visit here- i felt so sorry for #americans getting 2 weeks holiday/ #vacation from work. we get 5 weeks paid as standard in uk🇬🇧. living here now i realize they/we/they actually get so many extra days. this coming mon it’s #presidentsday. 🎉. no idea why; because i obvs haven’t started studying for 🇺🇸 #citizenship yet. but it shows how different our political systems are. the idea of having a #primeministersday wouldn’t fly at all uk/gb/england/scotland/etc..- who would we celebrate? most of them would be highly contentious. except maybe #churchill ? but post #metoo that’s even debateable! gary oldman’s #darkesthour sir winston was big, clever wordy, angry, scary & wouldn’t ever pass a breathalyzer test, even at breakfast - but was written as very in love with his steak at home @kristinscottthomas & kept his hands entirely to himself! the only nod we get to drunken or ‘sober’ inappropriate sexual behavior is gary, i mean sir w,  exposing himself to his young secretary after a bath- ‘in a state of nature’ played as simply eccentric & definitely for a laugh. it wasn’t so funny when the big man became #harveyweinstein; who also loved bathroom ‘shenanigans’ and did wear a robe. which didn’t restrain his #phallus, even sober, it seems. i actually think the usa system is better & family friendly. who doesn’t love a long weekend? especially in 😎 la. given impending 🌎joblessness from #automation &/ #artificalintelligence we need to move #capitalism to this 3 day weekend model asap to share jobs around more; & improve #mentalhealth. if we can wrest some of the capital from the few xxl #billionaire’s hands- it’s being concentrated in! this would work so much better for #society. but #margaretthatcher & #trump’s ilk don’t believe in that.. or really even #community. god this is getting political & dark 😂 to lighten up i propose a #queensday 🌈 holiday for #queens 👸🏿👸🏻🤴🏾👸 👑 🤴👨🏻‍🦰everywhere to be worshipped and adored. #godsavethequeen  @buckinghampalaceshop aka @kensingtonroyal @theroyalfamily gary & @giseleschmidtofficial ps i @wikipedia it- it’s really confusing! even dates 🤯

text:
rami malek opened up about the sexual assault claims surrounding bryan singer, who directed him in bohemian rhapsody.
. 
in a conversation at the santa barbara international film festival where he was honored for his portrayal of queen frontman freddie mercury, malek was asked about the recent allegations against the filmmaker. “my heart goes out to anyone who has to live through anything like what i’ve heard and what is out there,” malek told the audience. “it’s awful, it’s remarkable that this happens, i can appreciate so much what they’ve been through and how difficult this must be for them. in the light of the #metoo era that this somehow seems to exist after that, it’s a horrible thing.” malek said he found talking about his own experiences with the accused director to be difficult because he wanted the focus to be on the film and queen, but didn’t “want anyone to not feel like they can share their story.” “i’ve sat here and talked about how everyone deserves a voice and anyone who wants to talk about what happened with bryan deserves to have their voice heard,” malek told the crowd. “in my situation with bryan, it was not pleasant, not at all. and that’s about what i can say about it at this point.” malek reiterated that singer had been fired from the film. the director, however, had been removed from the production for asking to delay working on the film, and not for the abuse claims.

in january, singer was accused of having sex with four men who claim they were underage in an investigative feature on the atlantic. those weren’t the first claims to surface against singer: he was accused of rape in december 2017 by cesar sanchez-guzman, who was 17 at the time of the alleged incident.

text:
when it comes to sexual shame, we cannot rid or remove the shame we are holding... however, we can play with it...we can make art with it, and allow it to evolve into a practice of embodiment; learning exactly how we feel on the inside, instead of reliving the old tale in our heads. 
this type of trauma requires us to explore ways that protect and make us feel safe in our own skin. taking time to notice our body state and working in ways to connect and communicate. hopefully giving us a better recognition of what it is, we truly need from our partners to trust and feel out of harms way. .
.
.
⛓ @remishibari .
.
#metoo #recovery #shibari #embodiment #recognition #connection #communication #time #feel #listen #respond #evolve

text:
um assunto que eu sempre friso aqui, é a educação que precisamos dar aos nossos filhos para que possamos ter adultos conscientes e que saibam respeitar o próximo. 
se quisermos diminuir o preconceito, abusos, agressões, precisamos nos dedicar diariamente em educar nossos pequenos. 
não adianta muito querer mudar a safra que já está moldada. mais precisamos ter uma preocupação para que tipo de cidadão queremos no futuro. 
esse comercial da gilete que fala sobre a educação do machismo tóxico, é impecável e exemplifica o quanto a educação é negligente quando os homens são ensinados que ser macho é espancar, humilhar, ser anti solidário  com a dor do outro e etc. 
a educação que os pais do  meu abusador deu  foi na verdade total falta de respeito, de empatia, ele não sabe sequer o que é amor próprio. 
essa educação de que homem não pode ver uma mulher que tem que dar psiu, que dar cantada barata, que ser violento, bater é sinônimo de ser machão. e se tu não segue o rótulo, é ridicularizado pelos amigos. 
mais a mudança já começou e cada um de nós temos fundamental participação nisso. não se cale, lute por respeito. e você que é mãe, se volte a educar seu filho para ser diferente. respeitar uma mulher, não cantá-la quando a ver passar, dizer não aos amigos casados que gostam de trair suas esposas não o farão menos macho.  os homens de caráter precisam deixar a vergonha  de lado e começar a reprimir esses ditos “machões” que de machão não tem nada.  homens precisam parar de rir de violência. os homens precisam se responsabilizar pelas ações de outros homens. os homens precisam começar a se envergonhar pelas atitudes dos seus. 
ensine valores aos seus filhos, converse. seja exemplo. pois@os garotos vendo hoje, serão o futuro do amanhã. 
marciana bezerra. .
.
.
.
.
.

text:
#bookmail #bookmailisthebestmail
💖
thrilled for this early reader copy of why we lie by the inimitable @amyimpellizzeri 
coming march 5, 2019! pre-order now! 📚
why we lie examines the unexpected consequences of those who tell the truth about abuse and those who lie, and asks the question: is the truth always worth the cost?
authored by former biglaw litigator, two-year d.c. federal court clerk, amy impellizzeri's why we lie exposes the core of the #metoo movement in the legal/political realm--where powerful men have long been given a pass on criminal behavior, and victims have been discounted even within their closest circles.
📚
rising star politician and lawyer, jude birch, is clearly keeping secrets about his past from his wife. jude has been the bystander of a seemingly gang-related shooting, but as the secrets kept since law school unravel--with the help of a zealous news reporter and the capitol police--his wife realizes he might not have been an unintended victim after all. meanwhile, she makes every effort to clamp down a past marked by abuse and lies, and even a false accusation that still haunts her.
.
.
.
.
#tallpoppybloggers
#tallpoppywriters #amyimpellizzeri 
#arcreview #bookstagram #booklove #booksofig

text:
vad gör du för att vara snäll mot dig själv? 
frågan kom från min psykolog som satt mitt emot mig. jag blev så överrumplad av mitt eget svar att jag tystnade snabbt. 
jag hade precis suttit och ifrågasatt medans jag grät öppet hur är det möjligt att jag inte ägde mina tankar min röst min kropp mitt liv?? hur kunde jag bli så hjärntvättad och hur kunde han få mig att känna mig så värdelös att han kunde trampa på mig om och om igen😢 
ja jag är en analyserande person ska helst ha svar på det mesta för att behålla min kontroll , men efter min terapi sist förstår jag att jag har kommit långt jag skäms inte längre för vad jag har varit med om jag kan prata öppet om det. däremot har jag inte accepterat vad jag har varit med om eller vem jag har varit får inte ihop det om jag ser på mig själv i dag! acceptans ’ det kommer att ta lite tid att läka.. för att gå vidare. mitt liv är fullt med oöppnade dörrar som gläntar på sig öppnar sig jag känner rädsla för vad som finns därbakom. jag kan inte kontrollera när min hjärna nu släpper fram minnena. 
men en stor skillnad jag äger min historia min röst mina tankar min kropp mitt liv det kan ingen ta ifrån mig någonsin igen. du är inte ensam 🙏❤️ tillsammans vågar vi. genom att dela med mig hoppas jag nå ut till många med min självbiografi. 
fotografelinnordin#

#takecontroll #motivationalspeaker#❤️

text:
wiecie, ile słów wypowiadamy każdego dnia? około 16 tysięcy. a co, gdybyśmy mogli powiedzieć ich tylko 100? 😳
•
#vox to wstrząsająca opowieść o świecie rządzonym przez mężczyzn, w którym kobiety mogą wypowiadać tylko 100 słów dziennie. i nie tylko wypowiadać, bo słowo pisane również ograniczono do minimum. nie masz dostępu do komputera i książek. byłabyś w stanie żyć w takim świecie? 🤯warto sprawdzić.
•
premiera już 27 lutego. mogę powiedzieć jedno - ta książka jest mocna i na długo pozostaje w pamięci. @wydawnictwomuza
•
ps tak się wczułam w pozowanie, że złapałam książkę do góry nogami. ale cii 🤫
.
.
.

text:
kids waiting patiently in the wings to perform their very modern zombie dance. their class wowed the audience with a very spooky, very unusual dance. 
another class of older students had all eyes on them while performing a mix of dance and martial arts with the only girl in the performance playing a harassed victim of boys teasing and bullying her. by the end of the dance she had successfully stopped her attackers and remained the only one standing while the perpetrators lay on the floor around her. with more than a nod to "eve teasing", the school showed just how progressive it can be by reminding girls they have power over harassment they often face.

text:
i think we all need reminders of positives, so this is mine right now for you:

i hope you remember always that you don't deserve to be hurt,  not ever--not even by yourself.

you do deserve to be treated with compassion, empathy, and love by others and by yourself.

i hope you take good care of yourself. and i hope you keep connecting with others. we need those connections. and we need to treat ourselves gently and kindly, as kindly and gently as we would a friend.

love to you all,
cheryl rainfield, author of scars, stained, hunted

p. s. if it helps you, feel free to download this video and play it whenever you need to. i mean every word.

i've uploaded it to youtube, too, in case that makes it easier for you to bookmark or download.

text_retweet: #repost  @ryan_marc_read  @vswolf -  @earthlove777  @erinrileycarrasco i didn’t become vegan because i didn’t like the way meat and dairy tasted. i became vegan because i hated the taste of cruelty and suffering. so many people don’t know this, so here’s the truth: all calves born in the dairy industry are “bi-products.” all dairy cows need to be pregnant to produce milk. they don’t just produce milk on their own. farmers then steal the milk meant for the calves and sell to humans to drink. most calves are taken from their mother within the first 24 hours and either slaughtered or if a boy, sent to veal sheds where they are isolated in a tiny shed for apprx 5 months and then slaughtered. female calves may be spared, but are destined to live the same life as their mother and between 4-5 yrs of age, are also slaughtered after a life of being confined, put on the rape rack and having their babies stolen over and over. their bodies are spent after years of milk ”production” and then their flesh is sold to meat eaters. in the wild, cows live upwards of 20 years. you’re not going to hear about this on mainstream media. why do you think that is? that’s the truth. that’s dairy and that is cruelty. just because you like the taste of cheese does not negate the fact that this is what you’re paying for. #februdairy #dairyfree #dairy #govegan #crueltyfree #meat #hamburger #burger #pizzahut #pizzapizza #ilovepizza #cheesecake #cheesecakefactory #cheesey #vegetarian #creamy #cream #creamcheese #dairyisscary #stopseparatingfamilies #burgerking #veggies #farmher #vegano #metoo #seperation #donttakeourplanetforgranted #februdairy

text:
someone wrote this to me. i got this from my email on this morning. this individual read my article on my brother being falsely accused of sexual assault and molestation at the age of 13. in my brother’s case, the individual who accused him was my stepmother against her than 9 year old daughter, whom admitted years later that nothing ever took place and my brother never touched her. she also stated that her mother,”made me say it.
this individual who wrote me understood and could relate to my article, as i am certain far too many can relate but the way the system is designed, they do not really care if there is no evidence, especially for that of the life of a black man or youth who is being accused. often times our own for selfish reasons will destroy a life out of their own self issues, which is the case for my brother whom still to this day is effected and countless other lives behind a lie created by others with no repercussions. this is another form of social injustice and we must change the narrative on this as well. we cannot continue to allow such and the individual making false accusations and charges just be allowed to walk away scot free and go on in life while the lie of such has destroyed a life. #falselyaccusedhelp #falselyaccused #falselyaccusedsomeoneofrape #changethenarrativekp #changethenarrative #voicesup #voiceofthepeople #voiceofthecommunity #bridgingthegap #urbancreativity #stopbullying #blackbypopulardemand #wedemandjustice #changestartswithin #rapeculture #metoo #stopliesaboutrape #rapeisnotajoke

text:
my existence is political activism -

my very existence is political activism. our very existence as queer poc in a white dominant world is political activism. many queer poc may not be aware of it, but our existence sparks a reaction, a dialogue, a conversation and explodes into a movement. it's political and it's activism.

text:
12 motivos para amar terry crews  famoso por sua atuação no seriado norte-americano "todo mundo odeia o chris", no qual interpretava o papel do hilário e controverso julius rock, o ator terry crews conseguiu ganhar a simpatia de muitos espectadores. mas, apesar de sua fama estar diretamente ligada às telas de tv e cinema, terry desbravou outros mundos bem longe da atuação — acredite se quiser.

1. você sabia que ele é um artista nas horas vagas?

2. ele já foi jogador profissional de futebol americano na liga esportiva nfl

3. ele marcou nossas memórias no famoso seriado "todo mundo odeia o chris"

4. e continua bombando na série "brooklyn nine-nine"

5. ele contribuiu para o movimento #metoo

terry fez declarações acerca desse movimento que combate o assédio sexual. ele discutiu o tema "masculinidade tóxica" e fez uma confissão surpreendente sobre sua experiência como vítima (sim, isso é verdade!). 6. ele e sua esposa, rebecca crews, formam o casal mais fofo que você verá hoje

7. ele comprou bebidas que tinham seus rostos desenhados

8. ele é um pai muito atencioso e sempre demonstra seu amor pelos filhos

9. terry já lutou nos ringues de "battle dome"

para quem não sabe, essa foi uma série de tv americana que unia elementos de competições atléticas inspiradas nos gladiadores dos estados unidos e muitas brincadeiras.

10. ele é um cara muito bem humorado e positivo

11. o euro-treino

12. ele realmente adora os seus fãs

um fã twittou essa foto de terry crews — como julius — em sua carteira, dizendo que esse era um lembrete para ele não gastar dinheiro sem necessidade. e, em resposta à brincadeira, terry resolveu imitar seu fã.

text:
day 1 of f.l.a.g course  course was very successful! today’s topic was strikes (how to do and how to defend) and sexual harassment 
theory: 5 stages of self defence, how to overcome fear, how to minimise risk of being targeted. 
next week we will be focussing on how to respond to a controlling attack (grabs chokes, pins, holds) and combining grabs and strikes and how to defend 
final week is how to use everything and anything as a weapon or equaliser or to aid your defence, and basics of weapons defence. 
if you want to drop in for one of these topics please do it’s £25 on the door. 
#fightlikeagirl #phoenixeyewta #metoo #womenselfdefense #fightlikeagirlcourse

text:
another christina lauren novel, also finished in the #24in48 for you guys today.  dating you hating you was an absolute riot to read. when two hollywood agents meet and sparks fly, they kind of test the waters in a romantic fling.  however, this comes to a halt when their agencies merge and both are suddenly competing for the same job.  the book's description starts with: "all's fair in love and war." if you've been following me for any length of time, you will find that i love strong, feminist ladies.  i love females who do their thing and don't let others stop them. this book addresses misogyny in the work place and it's such a needed issue to be discussed.  in the time of #metoo reading books that address these issues are necessary and important.  kudos to christina lauren for handling this topic and making me cheer so hard to the protagonist in her endeavors!

text:
@xxxtentacion ⚰️🏝️👨‍🎤
.
.
.
california. at the time of his murder in june 2018, he was also awaiting trial for a 2016 domestic-abuse case, in which he was charged with aggravated battery of a pregnant woman, domestic battery by strangulation, false imprisonment, and witness tampering. taking in the full scope of these events is difficult and overwhelming, so we’ve compiled a timeline to try to make sense of the situation.

pre-2014

1998–2011: xxxtentacion grew up in pompano beach and lauderhill in south florida. he lived with his mother, who he said “had it hard,” and sometimes with his grandmother. “my mom was just in situations where she couldn’t take care of me,” he said in an interview on the no jumper podcast. from a very young age, he got involved in violent situations. “i’ve been fighting since i was a kid,” he said. when he was 6, he tried to stab a man who was “messing” with his mother. he was also expelled from his first middle school for fighting.

in his early teenage years, he developed a passion for music. he was drawn to nu-metal and hard rock as well as rap, and tried to teach himself how to play the guitar and the piano. in middle school, he said his aunt and mother tried to encourage this interest by signing him up for chorus, but he eventually got kicked out of the program for punching a classmate.

2012–2014: xxxtentacion attends high school at piper high school in sunrise, florida, before dropping out in the tenth grade. around this time, he says, he recorded and released a song, but there is no record of it online.

sometime in 2013–2014, xxxttentacion spends around nine months to a year in a juvenile-detention center for a gun possession charge. during this time he meets fellow rapper ski mask the slump god. after being released, the two go on to collaborate on several projects.

text: youth mentor and sexual assault interventionist.  this is the last role i ever imagined i'd have. i was a wild child.  i wont tell young people what to do. i want to help them find their voice and self love. i want them to honor intuition.  i may tell a few warning stories but mostly just want to create a space where they feel safe to share and call me if they get in a pickle. god knows i know my way out of a pickle.  i want them to understand what healthy dating choices look like. i'm a very lucky lady i hope these teens are just as lucky. what kind of teenager were you? who did you look up to? who made it easy to be honest?  #mentor #youth #teens #teenager #datingviolence #guidance #mistakes #giveback #payitforward #safehouse #powerandcontrolwheel #sexualassault #domesticviolence #metoo #youthfulmistakes #survivor  #support #supportsystem #wisdom #wildchild #dontmesswithmygirls #gotyourbacklittleone #womensempowerment #whoruntheworld #girlpower

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."
dailyhunt

text:
the scarlet letter #angelicaliddell @teatroscanal 'a angélica liddell no le gusta “este mundo donde las mujeres han dejado de amar a los hombres”. lo proclama al comienzo de su nueva obra, the scarlet letter, libremente inspirada en la novela de nathaniel hawthorne. la francotiradora por excelencia de la escena española no ha firmado una vulgar adaptación de ese monumento literario, sino un texto que parte de aquella diatriba decimonónica contra el puritanismo estadounidense para cargar contra la última reiteración del feminismo en tiempos del #metoo. liddell denuncia sobre el escenario la “justicia de revista de peluquería” del movimiento, conducido por “misandras totalitarias” que no dudan en condenar “a quienes, con su perversión, nos hicieron más libres”. no lo expresa la propia directora, sino su álter ego escénico, aunque en su caso cuesta distinguir al doctor frankenstein de su criatura. y, para aclararlo, de nada sirve pedirle ayuda. hace meses que liddell dejó de conceder entrevistas, tal vez porque sus explicaciones no serían audibles en el clima actual. aun así, el programa del espectáculo contiene un texto firmado de su puño y letra que no deja lugar a dudas. “seguimos rebelándonos contra la violencia de la hipocresía moral en tiempos de puritanismo. hemos perdido en el arte la fuerza de la naturaleza salvaje para siempre”, escribe. “hemos ganado en pacatería, en estupidez y en embuste. la cobardía y la mojigatería son más agresivas que nunca. antes era la religión. ahora, la ideología”. para liddell, todo en la vida humana procede del deseo, “de un sucio y violento movimiento entre penes y vulvas, de una pasión irrefrenablemente violenta”. eso es lo que traducen sus pinturas vivientes, en la que se pasea entre machos desnudos con la letra a, de adúltera, zurcida en rojo sobre su vestido negro. su escritura teatral, ese recital tremendista, no ha cambiado mucho y sus rituales escénicos siguen siendo perturbadores.' 📝 #alexvicente
para @el_país #theatre #liddell #teatro #teatrosdelcanal #thescarletletter

text: 21 years ago  i failed at taking my own life. 21 years ago i should have gotten the help i needed. i fell through the cracks and continued my life in a blur. becoming a parent 9 years ago made me see a lot of ugly parts of myself that were not easy to except. the way i reacted towards my son was not okay. i thought to myself, ‘ if love my son then why do i act this way?’. 21 years after my failed suicide attempt i finally came to terms with the dark parts of myself. i learned that these behaviors were because of multiple traumas as a child & as an adult. i didn’t think i could continue on as a parent if i’m perfectly honest. i thought, ‘ i’m fucked up so i’m going to fuck my son up.’ i honestly had no where & no one to turn to. i felt very alone in my illness but i knew deep down my son deserved better. so i started to read about trauma & the effects it had on my brain. i started reading about triggers & how to deal with them. knowledge is power. and even though my mind thinks differently than most people it doesn’t make it wrong. it’s just who i am. 21 years later, at 40, i’m okay with who i am. and for the first time in 9 years i think i might be an okay parent. i just hope & pray that jude will be a happy, well adjusted man one day. and that he loves himself always. much love to all of you. be kind to yourself; your story isn’t over yet. the best is yet to come ❤️ #parenthood #mentalhealth #cptsd #projectsemicolon #suicideprevention #singleparent #selflove #knowledgeispower #metoo #recovery

text:
#netflix
por @imbatcat44

#dumplin es una maravillosa historia que nos habla de los estereotipos femeninos aún vigentes en nuestra sociedad.

esta película toma como temática principal los certámenes de belleza, los
cuales hasta la actualidad miden el valor de muchas mujeres. es cierto que existe un rechazo
por parte de algunos colectivos ante este tipo de actividades, sin embargo la película no critica
estos eventos, sino que los usa a favor para contextualizar y posicionar a sus personajes en las situaciones adecuadas.

la trama es simple, no se hace complicaciones al momento de presentar sus escenas, se
visualiza con mucho agrado y la buena química que hay entre los actores y actrices traspasa la
pantalla. tiene un estilo similar a #sierraburgerssisaloser, pero menos romántico. aquí la protagonista no lidia con un amor imposible, sino con la búsqueda de un lugar en el mundo y el significado de su existir. uno de los puntos más resaltantes es que no se trata de un pesado drama lleno de lágrimas, sino de un metraje reflexivo y motivacional que deja una bonita enseñanza al final de todo.

no es una novedad que se toquen estos temas, hay muchísimas series y producciones cinematográficas que tratan sobre la aceptación corporal, no obstante "dumplin" logra manejar correctamente estos tópicos de forma directa y sin pretensiones gracias al gran optimismo que refleja su narrativa. "dumplin" cumple con el objetivo de entretener y hacer reflexionar sobre temas muy delicados
como es la obesidad y el bullying. la misma película se describe en la frase “revolución en tacones” y es evidente que el mensaje que trata de enviar es sobre la aceptación de nuestros cuerpos y el amor propio que todos deberíamos tener.

puntaje: 7/10

#cine #película #movie #film #jenniferanniston #review #metoo #cine2018

on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
wow.  you guys, i talked about my journey to a large group of people for the first time thursday.  at my workplace.  the audience included the man i love, colleagues, and former and current students.  i felt as if i stood there naked. .
immediately after i was unsure whether or not i had done the right thing.  like when you tear a band-aid off and realize that it hurt like heck, but it's too late.  i found it impossible to read the audience response.  i couldn't tell if they were extremely uncomfortable, in complete disbelief, or deep in reflection. .
i was so tired afterward and i woke up the next morning feeling hungover, like i had been drunk the night before and done something really stupid.  i still feel kind of raw and definitely exposed and like i want to run far away. i wonder if adam and eve felt like this when they realized they were naked... .
i won't run away, but that instinct is sure there.  i know that i have an imperative to share my story.  it sure is easier to do it from behind a keyboard than in a room full of people. ❤️
.
#livingoutloud #livingmybiggestlife #heartwork #hardwork #healthjourney #fearisaliar #metoo

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
guten morgen meine lieben 😊

ich möchte kein mitleid oder so,ich möchte ein zeichen setzen. 
ich möchte nicht länger schweigen,ich will wege zeigen um das leid zu beenden.
heute geht es um häusliche gewalt.

mit 18 jahren traf ich einen mann und verliebte mich sofort ihn ihn. er war so lieb die beziehung toll also am anfang zumindest. 
wir zogen nach 1 jahr beziehung zusammen,wir verlobten uns und wollten ein kind. 
hört sich doch toll an oder?

doch dann wendete sich das blatt,er began regelmässig sehr viel zu trinken und hatte ganz komische freunde aufeinmal,die auch sehr viel getrunken haben.

immer wenn er getrunken hat und heim kam und ihn irgendwas nicht gepasst hat,schlug er mich. nein er schlug nicht nur er verprügelte mich. er ging mit allen auf mich los was er fand.
er stach auch mit einen messer auf mich ein. er erniedrigte mich. er erzwang sich alles... ich verlor all meine freunde weil ich mich nicht mehr gemeldet hab,traute mich nicht mehr zu meinen eltern nach hause,bin zum schluss auch gekündigt worden weil ich nicht mehr auf die arbeit gehen konnte. wie auch. ich sah ja immer aus als hätte ich nen autounfall gehabt. 😳

mein weg aus den teufelskreis 
als er mich wieder verprügelte und ich verzweifelt nach hilfe schrie,kam die polizei,sie retten mich. doch wer hat sie gerufen? es war meine nachbarin der ich bis heute so dankbar bin,den sie rettete mir das leben. 
bei der polizei erzählte ich zum ersten mal alles was geschah.
ich wurde ins krankenhaus gebracht,ich hatte ein gebrochenes jochbein,meine nase war gebrochen,hatte eine schwere gehirnerschütterung,mehrere rippen waren gebrochen und würgemale am hals.
auch von missbrauch fanden sie spuren.

ich hab ihn dann angezeigt und mir hilfe beim weißen ring gesucht und bin erstmal in ein frauenhaus gekommen. 
wenn auch ihr so erfahrungen machen müsst,gemacht habt,egal ob frau oder mann. ihr seid nicht alleine!! #gutenmorgen #häuslichegewalt #gewaltgegenfrauen #gewalt #gegengewalt #frauen #männer #ihrseidnichtallein #zeichensetzen #metoo #gemeinsamsindwirstark #hilfeholen #keineangst #öffnen #kämpfen #kämpferherz #blogger #blogger_de #ff4instade #communityfüralle #growverbindet #instafam1602

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
i'm these guys!! i had no homecoming date either, just hugged the wall.

never felt like i belonged or one of the cool, popular kids.

the all american guy: tall, dark, handsome or blonde hair, blue eye jock or whatever that cliche saying is what people want.

i didn't fit those categories in school. i did have friends that are labeled as nerds but hey these people have feelings!

this is why i am a voice for my daughter monica who has autism, what society calls different!

i know what's it's like to be left out. 
under my watch i choose to educate, stand up for my people's, include them to experience things everyone else does!

p.s. if you have ever felt judged, left out for looking or being different, comment these words: me too below: 👇

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."
dailyhunt

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: ooit liep ik laat op de avond over straat in wenen. langs het museumkwartier. in de verte kwam een man alleen aangelopen. bruno ganz, de geniale acteur. ik denk dat ik 25 was en hij moet een jaar of 50 zijn geweest. ik had iets poëtisch moeten zeggen maar zei in rudi carrel deutsch: ich vind sie ein sehr schöne mann. er was niemand op straat, behalve wij. hij glimlachte beleefd en liep snel door. ik hoop dat hij zich niet bedreigd voelde en daar een #metoo beleefde. hij is niet meer onder ons, maar ik zou iedereen aanraden om een van zijn films te kijken #greatactor #inspiratie #enjaookeengoeiehitler #nazispelenkoniewel #brunoganz

text:
andy warhol said - “in the future everybody will be famous for 15 minutes” 
and thank fuck for that. 
fame (and elitism) only works on the concept that it is scarce and that it is “special” and that the people that have it are somehow better than you. so we tuck and starve and shame and dedicate ourselves to this falsity. 
to isolate or seperate yourself from your sameness, connection and similarity to other humans is the first cause of illness. it causes fear and anxiety and loneliness - whether u are the one isolating - or the one being isolated. (look at racism for example - i mean really! what a ridiculous fucking concept that was ... don’t even get me started on religion! )
the people that make diamond rings know that if they aren’t seen as “rare” they will lose their value in society ( when we all know they are just compressed shiny coal) 
now the “elite” might not want to give up their power - but you certainly don’t have to believe that you are lacking in yours! 🤩❤️⭐️💥
things like instagram and social media (used correctly)  help pull down and tear apart this disconnect - as does yoga, music, art, nature, reading, sharing, family, singing, loving, laughing, lifting each other up, supporting small business, sharing posts on things we believe in, meditation, drinking cups of tea, making time for each other, slowing down and valuing each other. the rich, the poor the old, the fat, the skinny, the ugly, the sick, the happy, the famous, the hermits, the extroverts and the introverts....
deep down we are all coal and diamonds - and even if we forget sometimes - we can never ever ever be disconnected from each other or the true source of life - ❤️🙏
it’s impossible 
xx (an excerpt from my book - the empire is falling - out soon!) xx

the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

text:
feminists don't wear pink (and other lies) amazing women on what the f-word means to them by scarlett curtis
.
.
description:
.
in an age of constant controversy over women’s issues, including the #metoo movement and the likes of trump and kavanaugh scandals, it is with perfect timing that a new collection of stories on feminism is welcomed into the publishing world.

curated by scarlett curtis, a journalist and activist, feminists don’t wear pink (and other lies) brings together 52 women to talk about exactly what the ‘f-word’ means to them. these amazing women include: authors such as dolly alderton (everything i know about love) and helen fielding (bridget jones’s diary); actresses including saoirse ronan, emma watson, and keira knightly; youtubers zoe sugg and tanya burr; and a whole host of other empowering female figures with a story to tell.

not only does it contain a plethora of recognisable names from all different fields, the royalties from every sale of the book go to girl up, a global leadership development initiative that strives for gender equality and achieve a world where every girl has the same opportunity as the next person, regardless of race, religion, ethnicity, sexuality, age or ability.

the book is split into different sections, with five main elements detailing the pathway to understanding feminism – epiphany, anger, joy, action, and education. there is also a ‘poetry break’ halfway through, full-page quotes, suggestions of further reading from emma watson (‘our shared shelf’) and, finally, a few lined pages at the back to jot down any notes you have while reading or inspiring quotes you want to remember.
this book combines everything you need to know about feminism in one handy volume that you can dip in and out of at your leisure. it isn’t there to judge you for not knowing as much about feminism as you feel like you should, or to overwhelm you with so much knowledge on the vast topic that you have to try and wade through to get some sort of understanding from it.
it also hopes to (and arguably successful in its quest to) eliminate the common misconceptions of the term. curtis herself says that she used to think she didn’t want to be

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin

text:
were you alone for valentines day?

i used to feel like that at one point in life. then i realised something. 
a relationship will fail 99% of the time because people stop looking after the seed you plant within the first few months. "what seed james?" the seed that gets planted when you first lay eyes on each other. the little sprout that emerges when you first hold hands. the leaves that bloom when you have the first kiss. 
months into this magical experience we put a glass ball around our little tree. we deprive it of the nutrients it needs.

we start to feel complacent and stop making effort. we feel like we own our other half. 
shatter the glass around that little tree...
let it breathe, nurture it and allow it to flourish once more.

realise you will never own anybody and you can only bring someone into your life when you are fully whole in yourself.

here's a news flash.

you have been and always will be whole.

if you felt alone yesterday do not worry. the time is coming and it will come into your life when you are ready. work harder on yourself until then.

tweet_full:
were you alone for valentines day?

i used to feel like that at one point in life. then i realised something. 
a relationship will fail 99% of the time because people stop looking after the seed you plant within the first few months. "what seed james?" the seed that gets planted when you first lay eyes on each other. the little sprout that emerges when you first hold hands. the leaves that bloom when you have the first kiss. 
months into this magical experience we put a glass ball around our little tree. we deprive it of the nutrients it needs.

we start to feel complacent and stop making effort. we feel like we own our other half. 
shatter the glass around that little tree...
let it breathe, nurture it and allow it to flourish once more.

realise you will never own anybody and you can only bring someone into your life when you are fully whole in yourself.

here's a news flash.

you have been and always will be whole.

if you felt alone yesterday do not worry. the time is coming and it will come into your life when you are ready. work harder on yourself until then.

text_retweet:
#repost @freedom_faction
・・・
#popefrancis on tuesday publicly acknowledged the scandal of priests and bishops sexually abusing nuns and vowed to do more to fight the problem, the latest sign that there is no end in sight to the #catholicchurch’s abuse crisis — and that it now has a reckoning from the #metoo movement.

francis admitted to the problem for the first time in public during a news conference while returning to #rome from the #unitedarabemirates. the acknowledgment comes just two weeks before he hosts an unprecedented gathering of bishops to craft a global response to the scandal of priestly predators who target children and the superiors who covered up the crimes.

francis was asked about priests who target adult women — the religious sisters who are the backbone of the catholic church’s education, health care and social service ministries around the globe — and whether the holy see might consider a similar universal approach to combat that issue. “it’s not that everyone does this, but there have been priests and bishops who have,” francis told reporters. “and i think that it’s continuing because it’s not like once you realize it that it stops. it continues. and for some time we’ve been working on it.” “should we do something more? yes. is there the will? yes. but it’s a path that we have already begun,” francis said.

the issue has come to the fore amid the catholic church’s overall reckoning with the #sexualabuse of minors and the #metoo-inspired acknowledgement that adults can be victims of abuse whenever there is an imbalance of power in a relationship. in the past year, the associated press and other media have reported on cases of abused nuns in #india , #africa, #europe and #southamerica — evidence that the problem is by no means limited to a certain geographic area.

in november, the organization representing all the world’s female catholic religious orders, the international union of superiors general, publicly denounced the “culture of silence and secrecy” that prevented nuns from speaking out and urged sisters to report abuse to their superiors and police... 🖐🏾more in @freedom_faction 👇🏾#pedogate #pizzagate #spiritcooking

text:
me too - «я тоже» или «и я»
⠀
но меня больше интересует фраза «me-too product»
обожаю английский за то, что в нем можно так играть с сочетаниями слов. кстати, в английском есть глагол, который обозначает выдумывание новых слов
coin (как монетка)
⠀
в фильме «джобс: империя соблазна» me-too product перевели как «вторичный продукт», но мне кажется эта фраза не передает всего смысла, всех эмоций данной фразы.
⠀
а как бы вы перевели фразу
“i don’t want to make a me-too product”???
жду комментов 😉
⠀

text_retweet:
⬆⬆@dancingwithdarkness_ ✨✨
_
reposted from @dancingwithdarkness_ -  posting this as a note-to-self for myself and anyone else who needs the reminder. ✨
.
.
so often we guilt ourselves for taking a stand, asserting a boundary, or doing something to protect our mental health. we prioritize the feelings of others over the safety of ourselves because we want to avoid conflict or don’t want to “hurt someone’s feelings”. in the end we end up suffering more mentally and emotionally by repeatedly allowing someone to harm our mental health and that needs to stop. ✨
.
.
last night i took a huge stance in addressing something that has been impacting me, my mental health, and my career for far too long. it was terrifying but it was also liberating. i took the first step towards reclaiming my freedom and extricating myself from a toxic situation. i don’t yet know how it will turn out but i am so grateful for the support network i have helping me through this scary and difficult time. ✨
.
.
the decision to stand up for myself and speak out against the situation has caused me insurmountable angst, but i can honestly say that opening up to the right people who are going to help me find a solution has been essential in lessening my anxiety. i am holding true to my beliefs and advocating for my rights and my mental health. it isn’t always easy, but it sure as hell is worth it. ✨
.
.
if you find yourself in a similar situation, please know that i am alongside you in the trenches. it can seem daunting and scary when you’re facing it alone, but i promise you that reaching out will make it feel more manageable. as my best friend always tells me... “everything is figure-out-able”. ✨
.
.
be brave, warriors and don’t be afraid to set those boundaries and stick to them. ✨ #metoo

text:
lucky to have a mother who wakes me up (litterally) for the important things, the last morning in aus i danced on the beach at sunrise. we were hundreds of womxn dressed in red for v-day (valentines day co-opted to vagina day by local and global movements) as we remembered those femmes that have been killed at the hands of a patriarchal and racist society and celebrated those who are still standing. through the singing and speaches the rain bucketed down drenching us all a much needed water for the parched summer, mixing with the tears of many. 
im grateful that this is being remembered and celebrated, that this is uplifting and exciting for me... now lets let our celebration flow over to communities in need. lets put our money where our mouth is.

below is a link to an organisation that supports criminalised women and girls, and their children, both inside and outside prison in australia. a large percentage of this population is indigenous. 
https://sistersinside.com.au/about/support-us/

name: Tiana Hemlock-Yensen
tweet_full:
lucky to have a mother who wakes me up (litterally) for the important things, the last morning in aus i danced on the beach at sunrise. we were hundreds of womxn dressed in red for v-day (valentines day co-opted to vagina day by local and global movements) as we remembered those femmes that have been killed at the hands of a patriarchal and racist society and celebrated those who are still standing. through the singing and speaches the rain bucketed down drenching us all a much needed water for the parched summer, mixing with the tears of many. 
im grateful that this is being remembered and celebrated, that this is uplifting and exciting for me... now lets let our celebration flow over to communities in need. lets put our money where our mouth is.

text:
همیشه با دیدن  این دوتا بازیگر یاد گذشته می افتم وقتی که من خیلی دوست داشتم بازیگر بشم و خانواده به هیچ وجه اجازه نمی دادند...منم مجبور بودم از اطرافیان بخوام کمکم کنند. توی این اطرافیان یه هم دانشگاهی داشتم که می تونست به من کمک کنه و من هم مثل همیشه که فکر میکردم همه مثل خودم هستند واگه کاری از دستشون بربیاد برای دیگران انجام میدهند به پیشنهاد یکی از دوستانم ازش کمک خواستم 
نتیجه این شد: مادیات، معنویات، و چند جمله قصار:
تو قدت کوتاه نمی تونی بازیگر بشی از در هر دفتر سینمایی بری تو بهت می خندن هیچ بازیگری کنارت بازی نمی کنه دوربین هم نمیشه از پایین گرفت اندام خانوما دفرمه میشه پاشنه بلند هم نمیتونی پات کنی یه وقت می خوای بدوی نمیشه...کلا تو با این فیزیک به درد این کار نمیخوری😐 (لازم به گفتن نیست چقدر از اعتماد به نفس من نابود شد و من با سن کمم باور کردم) 
هیچ وقت برای رسیدن به آرزوها و اهدافتون از آدمهای تنگ نظر و منفعت طلب درخواست کمک نکنید هیچ وقت از دوست داشتنی ها و محدودیتتاتون با آدمهایی که پر از عقده هستند صحبت نکنید.این جور آدما فقط دزدخوشبختی هاتون هستند و شما رو از رویاهاتون دور می کنن.
#metoo
#زن#lie

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

text:
i feel like i always look better in pictures than i do in person 😅 i think we all suffer with body dysmorphia to some degree, especially if you suffer from conditions like anxiety and depression like me. we all have internal struggles that everyone else is blind to but it consumes our lives. these past few months have been so hard, and staying consistent with my goals has become increasingly difficult, in and out of the gym. i know most of you know me as the strong one or the tough one. most of you aren't aware of my internal struggles because i don't make them know. just know you can be strong while dealing with mental illness 💪🏼 i believe in you all, because i believe in me. if i can overcome what ails me, y'all can too! 🤗 there's an unhealthy stigma of just hiding our mental health, people will be a lot more understanding if they just open up to one another even just a little bit.

on that note, i still think i look good 😎 however, there's always room for improvement! i love lifting weights because it's so empowering. not only as a woman, but as a human being in general. i know i can't control what goes on inside of my body, but i definitely can control the outside. i can change my environment and change my habits to live the healthiest life i can. i love going to work and being around people who keep it real and fun at the same time. 😄 i am so grateful for the people around me, especially those who go out of their way to check up on me! thank you guys so much! 💚

text:
what do we owe the survivors of sexual assault?

the victims of sexual assault are never to blame. no does not mean yes, and silence does not mean yes. consent can be revoked at any time. the best way to prevent rape from happening is to teach people to not rape. you do your best to keep yourself safe, by sticking with groups and being aware of your surroundings at all times, but you should not have to live your life accommodating for someone’s lack of self-control. we need to protect the survivors of sexual assault rather than shaming them into hiding. we owe them at least that much. 📷:im 🖊:im

.

text:
the buzz of the lights. that is all you can hear in this big #gymnasium, the buzz of the lights overhead and the sound of #brenda tracy’s voice, which remains steady even as she begins to cry.

her gaze shifts to the floor, if only for a moment. standing alone on an empty #basketball court, she straightens up and looks at the hundreds of people watching from the stands.

dressed in a black t-shirt and jeans, tracy resumes telling them about the night so long ago when she stopped by a friend’s apartment. she recalls the #football #players who were there, how they persuaded her to have a drink, how she passed out a short time later. “the first time i regained #consciousness, i became immediately aware i was laying on my back on the floor,” she says. “i was #naked and i couldn’t move my arms or legs.” the man on her left tried to force her to have oral #sex. so did the man on her right. “so i turned from them and looked up and the third man was #raping me,” she says. “and i remember feeling like i was trying to say or yell ‘stop.’” twenty years later, this is what the 45-year-old mother of two does, traveling the country to stand before strangers and share her most awful memory. she has appeared before 110,000 fans at #michigan’s football #stadium and 15 or so players on a basketball team. this crusade, which started years before the #metoo movement, takes her any place where people will listen.

on this night, at sacramento state, the #school has made attendance #mandatory for all of its athletes. a half-hour earlier, the 500 or so young men and #women walked in chatting, laughing, searching for friends to sit beside; now they have fallen quiet, leaning forward, some of them lowering their heads.

tracy has no memorized speech, no notes or litany of #statistics about #sexualviolence in #america. she hits her #audience with something different: sheer honesty, a graphic and unflinching #description of that night.

https://www.latimes.com/sports/more/la-sp-col1-brenda-tracy-20190207-htmlstory.html

#popefrancis on tuesday publicly acknowledged the scandal of priests and bishops sexually abusing nuns and vowed to do more to fight the problem, the latest sign that there is no end in sight to the #catholicchurch’s abuse crisis — and that it now has a reckoning from the #metoo movement.

francis admitted to the problem for the first time in public during a news conference while returning to #rome from the #unitedarabemirates. the acknowledgment comes just two weeks before he hosts an unprecedented gathering of bishops to craft a global response to the scandal of priestly predators who target children and the superiors who covered up the crimes.

francis was asked about priests who target adult women — the religious sisters who are the backbone of the catholic church’s education, health care and social service ministries around the globe — and whether the holy see might consider a similar universal approach to combat that issue. “it’s not that everyone does this, but there have been priests and bishops who have,” francis told reporters. “and i think that it’s continuing because it’s not like once you realize it that it stops. it continues. and for some time we’ve been working on it.” “should we do something more? yes. is there the will? yes. but it’s a path that we have already begun,” francis said.

the issue has come to the fore amid the catholic church’s overall reckoning with the #sexualabuse of minors and the #metoo-inspired acknowledgement that adults can be victims of abuse whenever there is an imbalance of power in a relationship. in the past year, the associated press and other media have reported on cases of abused nuns in #india , #africa, #europe and #southamerica — evidence that the problem is by no means limited to a certain geographic area.

in november, the organization representing all the world’s female catholic religious orders, the international union of superiors general, publicly denounced the “culture of silence and secrecy” that prevented nuns from speaking out and urged sisters to report abuse to their superiors and police... 🖐🏾more in @freedom_faction 👇🏾#pedogate #pizzagate #spiritcooking

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, suppoing him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
eight days to #oscars 🎬

this year, two movies about #british queens are up for oscars (unless you also count #bohemianrhapsody which admittedly is about a british #queen as well). mary queen of scots didn't live up to the initial promise and ended up with two nominations. the favourite, however, has gained major momentum. 
it started off as a critical hit that was written off as too artsy to really be in contention. gradually, it has reached dark horse status. the film now has a serious shot at an upset in coveted categories such as picture and supporting actress.
it helps the movie's case that it's so sharply in tune with the #metoo era, and that it has three of the greatest thespians of our generation chewing the scenery like nobody's business. this one fires on all cylinders.

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
an ode to liberated women -  @sketchesartofficial 
liberation is different for every woman and it is only upto her what she defines as liberation in her journey. here we show a journey that starts from a past rooted in pain: a kind of pain that gives one depth, and moves towards healing: here there are breaths to be taken and a lesson to be recalled. lesson that height is just as important as depth to create balance and height cannot be reached without tending to the wounds that the depth brought with it. finally, the ladder to liberation: giving your emotions the worth they deserve, growing out of the societal expectations, choosing to not let yourself be defined by anyone or anything else other than yourself, and eventually rising above own self image as well to open your inner eyes to see how limitless you are. we chose a girl to reflect this journey of rising above because we believe it starts with her. she represents & educates the family, leads the community to health, and will eventually walk the world towards healing with her sensitivity as her strength and vulnerability as her armor.

#thesketches #anodetoliberatedwomen #metoo

text:
an ode to liberated women - the sketches

liberation is different for every woman and it is only upto her what she defines as liberation in her journey. here we show a journey that starts from a past rooted in pain: a kind of pain that gives one depth, and moves towards healing: here there are breaths to be taken and a lesson to be recalled. lesson that height is just as important as depth to create balance and height cannot be reached without tending to the wounds that the depth brought with it. finally, the ladder to liberation: giving your emotions the worth they deserve, growing out of the societal expectations, choosing to not let yourself be defined by anyone or anything else other than yourself, and eventually rising above own self image as well to open your inner eyes to see how limitless you are. we chose a girl to reflect this journey of rising above because we believe it starts with her. she represents & educates the family, leads the community to health, and will eventually walk the world towards healing with her sensitivity as her strength and vulnerability as her armor.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn
