text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

she’s called a downer.  the absolute pain and misery in her eyes shows she's been broken, over and over again. she doesn't look like she has one ounce of fight left in her. she knows what's happening but she doesn't know why. if i were her, i would be begging for my life to be over, too. defeat. her eyes are screaming absolute defeat.

she was forced to give her life to the dairy industry. they stole every drop of milk they could from her until her body was too worn out to profitably produce enough, all so you could have dairy milk, dairy cheese, dairy ice cream, dairy creamer. making a mindless choice is easy when you don't have to face misery in the eyes, isn't it?

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

an ode to liberated women -  @sketchesartofficial 
liberation is different for every woman and it is only upto her what she defines as liberation in her journey. here we show a journey that starts from a past rooted in pain: a kind of pain that gives one depth, and moves towards healing: here there are breaths to be taken and a lesson to be recalled. lesson that height is just as important as depth to create balance and height cannot be reached without tending to the wounds that the depth brought with it. finally, the ladder to liberation: giving your emotions the worth they deserve, growing out of the societal expectations, choosing to not let yourself be defined by anyone or anything else other than yourself, and eventually rising above own self image as well to open your inner eyes to see how limitless you are. we chose a girl to reflect this journey of rising above because we believe it starts with her. she represents & educates the family, leads the community to health, and will eventually walk the world towards healing with her sensitivity as her strength and vulnerability as her armor.

#thesketches #anodetoliberatedwomen #metoo

text:
​​#историичитателей. прислала надира мухамедова.

хочу поделиться своей болью. сегодня день влюбленных. муж «подарил» мне свидание с любовницей и избил за то, что я поехала за ним. ищу свидетелей, вдруг кто-то снимал на видео!

а пока моя история. муж начал мне изменять чуть ли не с первых дней свадьбы. хотя сам долго ухаживал и убеждал родителей... после свадьбы я заметила смски от любовниц – но он постоянно врал и отказывался признаваться. я ругалась, терпела, прощала, верила... но он не меняется.

у нас двое детей, живу в доме с его матерью. сестра мужа меня ненавидит – когда она приходит к маме в гости, постоянно ко мне цепляется: то убралась не так, то приготовила не так. настроила свекровь против меня: раньше всё было нормально, а сейчас почти не общаемся. однажды сестра решила устроить скандал и кинула в меня стеклянную рамку. рассекла руку, было много крови. я вызвала милицию, но тогда свекровь спрятала дочь, а участковому сказала, что я вру. все меня отговаривали подавать заявление. мои слова против слов свекрови, мужа и её дочери – я была бессильна. со временем рана на руке зажила – а в душе осталась.

к сожалению, родители тоже меня не поддерживают. говорят, что мой дом теперь – там. и отправляют обратно. я хотела развестись – но муж не даёт развод. при этом постоянно получает сообщения от любовниц (уведомления всплывают на экране телефона, невозможно не увидеть переписку), но каждый раз он врёт мне. терпела ради детей – но больше не могу так жить. я не заслуживаю такого отношения.

сегодня муж приехал с работы домой, искупался, побрился и уехал. сказал, что по делам. я вызвала такси, поехала за ним, чтобы получить доказательства измены. увидела, как к нему в салон садится девушка с подарком. я подбежала, не дала закрыть дверь – и стала кричать на него, зачем он гуляет с другими, а мне развод не даёт? он вышел из машины и начал бегать за мной. потом поймал и сказал, что поедем к моему отцу. я согласилась, но та девушка сидела внутри. мне пришлось ее вытащить из салона и сесть внутрь. а после этого... после этого он заблокировал двери и начал избивать меня. бил по лицу, по голове. я защищалась, начала драться с ним.
name: Не молчи

text: the @donttellmehowtodress social power exhibition against sexual assault is on @woofpackbangkok until feb 24th. the original exhibition of clothing worn by victims of sexual harassment and assault and celebrity photo exhibition launched in june of last year is still going strong and receiving so much amazing feedback and support. this time we’ve added some works of art by young artists and activists as well, namely nana wipaphan wongsawang @iamnanaaa seine kongruangkit @sseine and sirada chitvathananont from @thaiconsent community and a really creative and colorful  mural painted especially for this event by designer and street artist @jayoto. come on down to check it out, sign up for one of our free talks, workshops and panel discussion on this weekend and the next and join in the conversation. this is all part of our effort to raise awareness that around the issues of victim blaming and discrimination against women in gender-based violence. thank you everyone for  listening and for also speaking up. ❤️🙏🏻 #donttellmehowtodress #novictimblaming #norapeculture #sexualassault #metoo #timesup #speakup #womensrights #gbv #unwomen

text:
there's not a single woman nominated for director this year.

the organization has diversified its ranks in terms of race and gender, but when it comes to its biggest awards — best picture, directing, screenplay — it's still a boys' club.

remember the year of the woman? of course you don't, because there've been so many, not just in hollywood but in the country at large. each time a year is labeled one of change for females, it disappears into the miasma of memory because the change was never real.
the first yow came in 1992, when an unprecedented number of women were elected to the senate after the anita hill/clarence thomas hearings, prompting sen. barbara mikulski to scoff: "calling 1992 the year of the woman makes it sound like the year of the caribou or the year of the asparagus." oscar made yow its theme the following year, opening the show with a photo of 67 female winners and declaring, "oscar celebrates women and the movies." hollywood followed with several more yows — indeed, in the mid-1990s every year seemed like a yow thanks to three studios being run by women (sherry lansing, amy pascal and stacey snider). the most recent yow came in 2018 with the double whammy of the #metoo and time's up movements, fueling hope that perhaps — possibly, maybe — hollywood would never need another yow. if only that were true. certainly in the executive suites women have moved forward in leaps and bounds. but further down, change has been slow, as evident in the current oscar race.

academy president john bailey noted at the feb. 4 nominees lunch that more women have been nominated this year than ever before: 59 of the 212 nominees for the 91st oscars are female, up from 51 last year. true, there's a panoply of women filling less prominent categories such as live-action, documentary and animated shorts. but dig deeper and women are as rare in other categories as female members of the augusta national.

text: the @donttellmehowtodress social power exhibition against sexual assault is on @woofpackbangkok until feb 24th. the original exhibition of clothing worn by victims of sexual harassment and assault and celebrity photo exhibition launched in june of last year is still going strong and receiving so much amazing feedback and support. this time we’ve added some works of art by young artists and activists as well, namely nana wipaphan wongsawang @iamnanaaa seine kongruangkit @sseine and sirada chitvathananont from @thaiconsent community and a really creative and colorful  mural painted especially for this event by designer and street artist @jayoto. come on down to check it out, sign up for one of our free talks, workshops and panel discussion on this weekend and the next and join in the conversation. this is all part of our effort to raise awareness that around the issues of victim blaming and discrimination against women in gender-based violence. thank you everyone for  listening and for also speaking up. ❤️🙏🏻 #donttellmehowtodress #novictimblaming #norapeculture #sexualassault #metoo #timesup #speakup #womensrights #gbv #unwomen

text:
i have friends on twitter, like at sweetsoulkisses and at luv_n_adventure who helped support me through my first #nanowrimo on “a hard run into hell” book 4, the true story of my dad and i trying to save my mom from stage 3 cancer, the very same year my mom died.
i have friends like at sheplaysloud, who is the reason there even is a cookbook in the making. not only did she give me the suggestion for it but she gifted me the title as well, “sometimes i bake”.
i have friends like at fairycemetery who gives me a safe space to share without judgement and also makes me laugh so hard it’s like i’ve just done 250 sit ups. or at apocketsaint who read an early chapter of “twitter: stories from the underbelly” book and gave feedback, has read a few of my wattpad projects, and gave feedback on my first feeble attempts at audio readings of my own poetry. lol
i have friends like at crimson_snark who has probably read more of my works on wattpad than anyone else i know. she also helped with some early chapters of “twitter: stories from the underbelly”. i have the 26 beautiful people from twitter who went through my twitter book questionnaire to share their experiences and thoughts. or the 65 wonderful twitter people who allowed me to use their quotes in the book.
i have people like the courageous 7 sexual assault survivors who came forward to share their stories and thoughts by going through my not-so-fun #sexualassault questionnaire. i have the 49 amazing sexual assault survivors on twitter who kindly gave me permission to use their quotes in the #metoo #whywomendontreport #whyididntreport #notokay chapters.
i have more people than i will probably ever know of who showed up for me. and i hope i’ve turned that around to support and encourage others as well.
i dunno. i don’t have the normal life or normal friends i can meet for tea. but i am fortunate that i have a posse all over the world, thanks to social media, who step forward with their support of me and my writing. and there’s nothing more special and phenomenal than people like that.
© 2019 rantingsofagirl.com

text:
@ronwyden that townhall made me lose every bit of respect i had for you. i have been working with your office for a year and things have gotten worse. you don't hold those that violate federal law accountable and you clearly don't respect or want to hear minority stories told by our own voice. clearly you want to keep oregon white and only use minority and veteran stories as anecdotes and to pull at heart strings but you will be damned if we tell our own stories.  i am disgusted by that farce and your inability to hold a school that dictates to the va what they will and won't do and that is heavily funded by the va but everyone is too afraid to say anything to them. i was hoping tonight i  would find out you are more than talk sadly that is all you are.

text:
🇮🇳 क्या लिखा कुछ पता नहीं, बस अंदर से आवाज़ आई और एहसास छलक आए, मेरे भी कई  जान पहचान वाले सैनिक हैं, मैं न अंदर से स्तब्ध रह गया पुलवामा की घटना सुनकर, ये नेताओं के छिछले भाषण सुनकर, tv में ब्रेकिंग न्यूज़ देखकर न इन पर ही बड़ा गुस्सा आता है, इनको तो बहस का मुद्दा मिल जाता है। और कहाँ गायब हैं अवार्ड लौटने वाले, intolerance-intolerance चिल्लाने वाले, और कहाँ है वो human rights वाले जो किसी आतंकवादी के मरने पर हमारे जवानों को दोष देते हैं, हमारे देश में रहकर हमारे ही पीठ में छुरा घोपनें वाले। और ये  #metoo campaign वाले कहाँ गायब हो भैया??? कोई दिखता क्यूँ नहीं?? बस 2-4 मंत्री भाषण दे देंगे ये कहकर की "जो भी हुआ गलत हुआ हम इसकी कड़ी निंदा करते हैं।" साले सब के सब बरसाती मेंढक हैं। निंदा नहीं चाहिए, हमें चाहिए हमारे जवानों का बदला वो भी ऐसा बदला कि हर आतंकी का दिल फ़ौज़ी नाम से दहल उठे, उनकी रूह सैनिक देखते ही काँप जानी चाहिए।
इन आतंकियों को  सबक तो सिखाना ही होगा।
अब और नहीं अब और नहीं.. ❣️🇮🇳jai hind 🇮🇳❣️
🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳🇮🇳 🇮🇳❣️dedicated to our❣️🇮🇳 🇮🇳#indiansoldiers 🇮🇳 कुछ इस क़दर मुल्क से मुहब्बत है उनकी ,

वो जान भी हथेली पर रखकर मुस्कुराते हैं ,

अपनों से दूर अपनों की सुरक्षा की ख़ातिर ,

वो सर भी अपना सोंचों हँसकर कटवाते हैं ,

वतन के लिए जीते हैं वतन पर ही मरते हैं ,

वो तिरंगे से लिपटकर घर को लौट आते हैं ,

न धर्म, न जाति, न कोई क़ौम, न मज़हब ,

वो हिंदुस्तान के बेटे हैं जो फ़ौज़ी कहलाते हैं ! 🇮🇳- क़बीरा 🇮🇳 - kabiraaspeaks -

text:
the time i was thirsty...
.
.
i try to find inspiration in the little things.  i’ll be honest...i can’t always find it.  but i know i can be thirsty for it...like real thirsty.  i’ll check pod casts, books, articles, interviews, blogs, some of y’all posts, music, art...i mean i check all of it.  and i find it.  sometimes.  but that type of inspiration comes in waves, sometimes lasting for a minute and sometimes fleeting away just as quick as it came.  it’s not that it wasn’t good or motivational...it’s just that i’m always thirsty.  things i think about before i head to the studio tomorrow to record a few tracks.
.
.
we live a world full of thirsty people.  i’m one of them. you’re one of them.  we all are.  and let’s just be real...we’re all thirsty for something...some of us attention, some of love, some of us connection, and some of us are thirsty for something but have no idea what.  but if we’re gonna be thirsty for something let it be for something more...something more than love or attention.  let us be thirsty for inspiration...and i hope we never quench it.  and i hope we forever stay looking for it...searching for it.  and i hope one of the places we find inspiration isn’t a pod cast or a post, but inside of us. #loveyourself 😉💜✍🏾✨🎧🎼
.
.

text:
there is no "perfect victim" or "perfect reaction" to sexual assault. it often seems that no matter what i do, it is not the right thing. some people tell me that i just need to move on with my life, others say i am not "healed" because i keep "dwelling on what happened." people have told me to stop calling myself a victim and start calling myself a survivor. people have told me that i need to stop being so angry and that forgiveness is what will set me free. i am tired of being told by people who didn't experience what happened to me telling me how to respond. you have a right to your emotions and reactions.

comment below ⬇️ how have you coped with unsolicited "advice" and victim blaming?

text:
💰 unpack your debt💰 🔥free 5-day bootcamp to accelerate your way to a debt-free life 🔥

has debt gotten out of hand in your life? 
do you feel like having debt drains your energy, keeps you awake at night, even affects your health, your relationship, your quality of life??
having debt often feels so overwhelming that sometimes you lose hope that you’ll ever be able to pay it off.
and so you wait… for better circumstances, for better timing, for better income…and in a meantime, you get deeper and deeper into the debt-hole.
enough of this nonsense!!
it’s time to unpack your debt! it’s time to act on your desire to be debt-free.
at “unpack your debt” free 5-day bootcamp, you will
💰 uncover whether you developed an addiction to debt
💰 learn how to change your beliefs about you and debt
💰 receive guidelines, resources and support to act on your desire to be debt-free immidiately
💰 forgive yourself and focus on possibilities
how much time will it take you to repay your debt if you start now?
as quickly as you allow it! 
register for the unpack your debt bootcamp and live debt-free life.

text:
tonight i did cardio in order to stop running.
_________________________________________________ as contradictory as that sounds, hear me out. tonight, i got myself to the gym and did over a hour of cardio. i did that, even though my mind was urging me to escape reality through sleeping or drinking. 
now, that may not seem like much. but to me, that's a massive victory. i worked out to prove that i was no longer controlled by the past. i ran for over 60 minutes in order to stop running from my past. i'm through being stuck in the vicious cycles from past toxic encounters. i'm not going to hide behind alcohol, sleep, or silence anymore. 
i ran today in order to stop running from my past. i ran to find my voice and raise it against those individuals who have hurt and/or violated me 
yes, i am an activist for the therapeutic effects of physical activity haha. .
.
.
#therapy #workout #girlswholift #anytimefitness #platinum #cardio #workhard #proud #therapeutic #voice #growth #happy #support  #bossbabe #courage #kesha #speakout #metoo #activist

text:
"our traditional african values survived the middle passage, centuries of slavery, and even the lynch era.  but they did not survive popular culture.

popular culture normalizes degrading, unhealthy, and even dangerous sexual behaviors because poor girls or “girls from the hood” are taught that they have no value.  no worth.  not having a lot of money does not mean we have no worth.  being the descendants of slaves does not mean we have no worth.  having a history marred by sex slavery and exploitation does not define us.  those things were done to us.  they are not who we are.

according to ida b. wells, “during the slave regime, the southern white man owned the negro body and soul.” and it seems like the white man still does." click link in bio to read more. comment, follow, share!

text:
how #metoo is battling gender-based violence
#
the #metoo movement swept india last year when the bollywood actress tanushree dutta accused actor and filmmaker nana patekar of sexually harassing her in 2008 on the set for the film horn ok pleassss. in october last year, she also filed a first information report (fir) against him and others with police. it has been reported that patekar has denied the allegations and issued a legal notice to her to withdraw the allegations. dutta was also in the news more recently, putting a “curse” on film choreographer ganesh acharya, actor rakhi sawant and producer sami siddiqui for what she suggested was enabling the alleged abuse.these allegations made by such a well-known figure changed the course of the #metoo movement in india and opened the floodgates for many other women working in bollywood, the media, corporations and government to allege sexual harassment by high-profile and powerful men. social media platforms were flooded with #metoo stories and outrage, highlighting what has always been a taboo subject in india: the extent of harassment and violence against women, along with the deep-rooted injustice and inequality they face.the #metoo campaign has provided a gateway for indian women to vocalise the “enough is enough” message and…

#
the #metoo movement swept india last year when the bollywood actress tanushree dutta accused actor and filmmaker a patekar of sexually harassing her in 2008 on the set for the film horn ok pleassss. in october last year, she also filed a first information report (fir) against him and others with police. it has been reported that patekar has denied the allegations and issued a legal notice to her to withdraw the allegations. dutta was also in the news more recently, putting a “curse” on film choreographer ganesh acharya, actor rakhi sawant and producer sami siddiqui for what she suggested was enabling the alleged abuse.these allegations made by such a well-known figure changed the course of the #metoo movement in india and opened the floodgates for many other women working in bollywood, the media, corporations and government to allege sexual harassment by high-profile and powerful men. social media platforms were flooded with #metoo stories and outrage, highlighting what has always been a taboo subject in india: the extent of harassment and violence against women, along with the deep-rooted injustice and inequality they face.the #metoo campaign has provided a gateway for indian women to vocalise the “enough is enough” message and…

text:
impossible to have a non-meaningful and life changing interaction with @ryjlewis. ryan is leading @befreephilly to new heights and here is his definition of freedom: “you walk through the door of your apartment, house, etc. at the end of a long day. you take one big exhale, and the weight of what you carried throughout your day is released.

i look for ways to recreate this feeling outside of that situation. to me that feeling is freedom. it is in that moment where you feel safe and settled. it can also be defined as the feeling of being at home.

i have been able to find this feeling not only in places, but also, and more importantly, in people. there are a handful of things we feel comfortable doing exclusively in the security of our homes, and i look to fill my life with people who cultivate that same security.

next time you walk in to your house, notice how it feels. feels free, right?” 🏡

text:
i love that @tracidoula is such a fan of #knowyourrights. this is somebody with 20 years of experience in one of the more hostile birth environments: the state of alabama. she’s right, it’s not so much about the overt violence as it is the subtle, everyday, normalized ways birthing women and people are undermined, pressured, and not given choices. 🚨 this course is not about confrontation. it’s about empowerment. simply knowing the foundation on which your rights rest is a powerful confidence booster. knowing your leverage, feeling more in control, allows you to step out of fear and into a stronger, gentler, calmer place. ⛲️ check out the testimonials and other info at the bio link for know your rights: legal and human rights in childbirth for birth pros 📜 want ceus? it’s worth 1.5 contact hours through @ebbirth , an approved provider thru the ky nursing board. 💰 want a deal? know your rights is many dollars off this weekend and won’t be again for a while.

text:
this is 2019 amy. she knew the only way out was to go through it, so she did. my god, did she go through it! it was much harder than she expected it to be, but turning back wasn’t an option so she pushed through. when she came stumbling out the other side she wasn’t met with immediate joy like she had anticipated. she felt sad, confused, isolated, wronged, and angry, but becoming bitter wasn’t an option either so she pushed through. 
____
she spoke her truth, she allowed herself to fall apart, she leaned on her tribe to help her stand back up again, and she put all of her faith in god to lead her down the path of the life she was meant to live. 
___
2018 did not define her, but the emotional distress that comes from having the courage to speak up only to be met with disbelief because the perpetrator denied it and the only witness within ear shot chose to protect himself over doing the right thing, stays with a person for a very long time. 
___
her story is still unfolding, but every day she wakes up with a grateful heart for a fresh start where she gets to decide who to surround herself with and a deeper understanding that the energy she puts out into the universe is the energy she will get back. and you better believe it has been one of fierce determination for whole-hearted connections! 
____
this is 2019 amy. she’s as imperfect as she was the year before but her voice is louder and she stands tall with her shoulders back and her tits out. she’s going to be the best version of herself yet. she sees you and she wants that for you too, so she’s here for you if you need her. don’t be scared to reach out. 
___

jacket and tee: @evereveofficial 
pants: @hm 
____

text:
fans!!!! read this before you read try me not!!!! i hope this gets to most of you before you dive deep into my book, but this could be a trigger because there is rape in this book. if you feel you could be bothered or triggered by reading about it, pleaseeeeee don't read!!! i apologize for not mentioning that sooner but please understand i'm a first time author and still learning about this!!!! no hard feelings if you can't read/buy my book. rape is a serious thing and instead of speaking my opinions on social media, i talk about it through my writings. i have been on the receiving end of rape and if my story could help just one person, my job is done. please know that i'm not trying to bash or hurt/trigger anyone. i'm just using my gift to (hopefully) help, inspire, change, motivate someone. 
thanks for everything 😘😘😘😘 #triggerwarning #firsttimeauthor #rape #metoo #ihearyou #iwillusemygift

text:
**long post**
when i was 18, a classmate at nec raped me. i didn’t report it because just a few months prior, my friend reported and instead got in trouble for underage drinking and the rapist was not punished. i didn’t tell anybody except my closest friends, and i truly believed that it was somehow my fault, even though it was 200% the fault of the person who decided it was okay to treat another human being that way. i remember waking up in rage at 3 am, sobbing to close friends, because it was too much to process. even now, 6 years later, thinking about it makes my heart race and i break out in cold sweat. 
i wish that the nec community was more receptive to talking about this. i wish the school did not punish victims, but instead proactively protected their students. so @necmusic, i call to you to make better choices in the future, and take this seriously. your students come with hopes and dreams, and fostering musicians is not just about the performance. 
huge shoutout to @fishyinthesie for all the advocacy she has been doing, and for inspiring me to speak up about something i’ve hidden for 6 years. you are so brave for doing what you do and speaking up on behalf of all the nec students. ❤️
